{"by":"dominicq","id":47774897,"kids":[47774990,47775078,47775914,47777768,47775029],"parent":47773812,"text":"&gt; Fundamental in the dependency cooldown plan is the hope that other people - those who weren&#x27;t smart enough to configure a cooldown - serve as unpaid, inadvertent beta testers for newly released packages.<p>This is wrong to an extent.<p>This plan works by letting software supply chain companies find security issues in new releases. Many security companies have automated scanners for popular and less popular libraries, with manual triggers for those libraries which are not in the top N.<p>Their incentive is to be the first to publish a blog post about a cool new attack that they discovered and that their solution can prevent.","time":1776229657,"type":"comment"}